user
Round-0 fixes:

1. reconcile_remote_orphans now narrows to NotFound only (eden_storage.errors.NotFound). Any other Store.read_trial exception (DispatchError, transport-shaped, anything else) → leave the remote ref alone, log nothing, let the next startup retry. Spec-authoritative deletion only.

2. web-ui admin work-refs page now does read-before-display (fetch_all_heads when origin configured) AND remote-delete first, then local-delete. Stderr classification recognizes 'stale info' / 'rejected' (CAS mismatch → ?error=ref-changed) and 'deleting unknown ref' / 'remote ref does not exist' (?error=not-found). Pre-cutover (no --gitea-url) deployments fall through to the existing local-only path via the _repo_has_origin gate.

3. Three new public-path integration tests added in test_remote_integrator.py covering the indeterminate-push step-2 branches: remote-landed (4a+4b run via ls-remote read-back; original DispatchError re-raised), remote-absent (4b only; GitTransportError propagates), remote-diverged (4b only; mapped to RefRefused). Plus a fourth test for the fix in (1) — indeterminate Store.read_trial does NOT delete the remote ref. All 12 tests pass.

All gates green: ruff, pyright, full pytest (708 pass), markdownlint, and the three compose smokes pass locally end-to-end through Gitea.
