codex
1. High: the orchestrator still appears to refresh its private clone only once at startup, but `Integrator.integrate()` later promotes from that clone without fetching the implementer-pushed `work/*` branch first. [reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/cli.py:156](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/cli.py:156>) does the startup-only `fetch_all_heads()`, [reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/loop.py:64](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/loop.py:64>) just calls `integrator.integrate()`, and [reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py:137](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py:137>) / [reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py:360](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/reference/packages/eden-git/src/eden_git/integrator.py:360>) immediately require `trial.branch` and its objects to already exist locally. That contradicts the plan’s long-lived-clone freshness rule at [docs/plans/eden-phase-10d-followup-b-gitea-remote.md:274](</Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-10d-followup-b-gitea-remote.md:274>). Absent another fetch path outside the reviewed surface, the integrator clone can miss newly-pushed `work/*` refs and fail promotion.

The round-0 fixes themselves look good. The `reconcile_remote_orphans()` narrowing to `NotFound` is the right correction, and the web-ui admin work-ref flow now matches the intended remote-first model.

Overall assessment: not ready to ship yet. I would require one more revision: fetch the relevant `trial.branch` into the integrator clone before promotion, or otherwise refresh remote state on the integrate path, and add a regression test that proves promotion works from a private clone when the `work/*` ref was pushed after orchestrator startup. If there is already another code path doing that fetch outside the files above, point me to it; otherwise this remains a blocker.
